{"title":"Ari Cascade Peak Alloy Trail Bike Finally Updated, Super Affordable","link":"https://bikerumor.com/ari-cascade-peak-mountain-bike/","date":1715212875000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-1-1536x1024.jpg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1024\" alt=\"ari cascade alloy trail bike shown in the desert\" /></p>\n<p>Until now, Ari’s budget lineup had multiple models sharing the same frame, but different names based on spec and travel. Now, their entry point into full-suspension trail bikes is fully updated with a shapely new frame and a single name – The Cascade Peak.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Ari Cascade Peak’s frame is air- and hydro-formed to delivery a stiff, responsive frame with modern aesthetics. It’s most noticeable at the top tube and head tube junction, but note the seattube’s bulge and shaping, too. That effort gives it a better second water bottle placement, letting you get two bottles on all frame sizes.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The extra shaping and butting also saves a claimed 250g over straight gauge round tubes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"849\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4-1536x849.jpg\" alt=\"ari cascade alloy trail bike headtube shown from an angle\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4-1536x849.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4-297x164.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4-120x66.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4-768x424.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-4.jpg 1920w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It gets 135mm rear wheel travel, paired with 140mm forks. The suspension has their adjustable geometry GA Link, which can be used to convert it from a full 29er to a mixed wheel 29/27.5″ setup.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"769\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3-1536x769.jpg\" alt=\"closeup of ari cascade alloy trail bike frame\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3-1536x769.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3-297x149.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3-768x384.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-3.jpg 1920w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Standover height is lower, making it more maneuverable and allowing longer travel dropper seatposts.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It comes with UDH hangers and new epoxy-infused paint that’s tough and chip resistant.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>2024 Ari Cascade Peak specs, geo &amp; pricing</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5.jpg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"841\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-1536x841.jpg\" alt=\"ari cascade alloy trail bike shown from the side in mustard yellow color\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-1536x841.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-297x163.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-120x66.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-768x421.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-5-2048x1122.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cascade Peak Comp ($1,999)</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Suntour XCR 34/Raidon R</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Microshift Advent Drivetrain</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tektro 4 Piston Brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WTB i30 Wheels</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cascade Peak Elite | $2,499</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>DVO Diamond D3/Opal T2</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano CUES Drivetrain</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tektro 4 Piston Brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WTB i30 Wheels</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Cascade Peak Pro ($2,999)</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>DVO Diamond D1/Opal T2</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM GX Eagle Drivetrain</li>\n\n\n\n<li>SRAM DB Brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>WTB i30 Wheels</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1128\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6-1536x1128.jpg\" alt=\"ari cascade alloy trail bike shown from front angle in dark gray color\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6-1536x1128.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6-297x218.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6-120x88.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6-768x564.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-alloy-trail-mountain-bike-6.jpg 1761w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1444\" height=\"1043\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart.jpg 1444w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart-297x215.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart-120x87.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-ari-cascade-geometry-chart-768x555.jpg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Geometry is fully modern, getting Ari’s signature steep seat angle (78º) and slack head angle (65º), with about 20mm more reach than before. I’ve been riding the Pro model a bit, stay tuned for a review.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://aribikes.com/products/cascade\" target=\"_blank\">AriBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/ari-cascade-peak-mountain-bike/\">Ari Cascade Peak Alloy Trail Bike Finally Updated, Super Affordable</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Tyler Benedict","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"1974840f1b1601c04e0861cfa3c4f47b7596f6dec6904540d6f8f42cc95b63c9","category":"Cycling"}